nificent gift and marked the turning point in the history of the church.' His widow Lydia Blakeslee Pierpont added another thousand dollars at her own 1863 death nine years later — six thousand total, a remarkable sum for a mid-century Connecticut parish congregation."},{"number":2,"category":"family","header":"Wife Lydia Blakeslee outlived him by nine years","body":"Ebenezer married Lydia Blakeslee (born July 2, 1768) — daughter of Joel and Elizabeth Sackett Blakeslee. Lydia outlived him by nine years, dying July 22, 1863 in North Haven at age ninety-five, her own thousand-dollar bequest to the church supplementing his earlier five-thousand. The couple's combined legacy effectively endowed the North Haven Congregational Church mid-century operations."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Born and died North Haven, age eighty-three","body":"Ebenezer Pierpont was born in 1771 in North Haven Connecticut and died March 4, 1854 in North Haven at approximately age eighty-three. His entire life unfolded within his birthplace town — a stability characteristic of the eighteenth-and-early-nineteenth-century New Haven County Pierpont families. His wife Lydia would live to ninety-five, an extraordinarily long life for her generation."}],"slug":"ebenezer-pierpont-1771"},"HD1526":{"id":"HD1526","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":false,"generation_from_thomas":7,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false},"parents":{"father_id":"HD1429","mother_id":"X00490"},"birth":{"year":1795},"death":{"year":1821},"tags":[],"sources":[],"gender":"female","marriages":[],"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Roxana Pierpont","first_name":"Roxana","maiden_name":"Pierpont","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"nami